  "Superheavy elements are so short-lived that they are identified by their decay signatures — a specific chain of alpha decays producing known isotopes, confirming the parent element.": "",
  "The Sun converts about 600 million tons of hydrogen into helium every second. Why doesn't it run out quickly?": "",
  "The Sun has an enormous mass (~2 × 10³⁰ kg), enough fuel for billions of years": "",
  "The Sun absorbs hydrogen from other stars": "",
  "The Sun recycles helium back into hydrogen": "",
  "Fusion doesn't actually consume hydrogen": "",
  "The Sun's mass is about 2 × 10³⁰ kg. Even at 600 million tons/second, it has enough hydrogen to sustain fusion for approximately 10 billion years total.": "",
